{'prompt': 'Extract the relevant fiscal year actual adjusted diluted EPS, prior-year adjusted diluted EPS, full-year adjusted diluted EPS guidance/outlook ranges for FY2023 and FY2024, and FY2025 guidance/outlook from these General Mills SEC exhibit press releases. For FY2023 use both the FY2022 release providing FY2023 outlook and FY2023 results release; for FY2024 use the FY2023 release providing FY2024 outlook and FY2024 results release; for FY2025 use the FY2024 release providing FY2025 outlook and the FY2025 Q3 update. Quote exact passages. Documents:

FY2022 / FY2023 outlook: {{sec_gis_fy2022}}

FY2023 results / FY2024 outlook: {{sec_gis_fy2023}}

FY2024 results / FY2025 outlook: {{sec_gis_fy2024}}

FY2025 Q3 update: {{sec_gis_fy2025_q3}}'}

{'prompt': 'From the FY2023, FY2024, and FY2024 Q3 documents, extract every sentence/passages mentioning full-year adjusted diluted EPS outlook/guidance and actual adjusted diluted EPS. Include the dates/titles if present. Documents:
FY2023 results/outlook: {{sec_gis_fy2023}}
FY2024 results/outlook: {{sec_gis_fy2024}}
FY2024 Q3: {{sec_gis_fy2024_q3}}
FY2025 Q3: {{sec_gis_fy2025_q3}}'}

{'final_result': 'Using General Mills’ most recent full-year Adjusted Diluted EPS guidance before each fiscal year ended, General Mills beat guidance **2 times in the past 2 completed fiscal years** — fiscal 2023 and fiscal 2024.

| Fiscal year | Latest full-year Adjusted Diluted EPS guidance before year-end | Actual Adjusted Diluted EPS result | Beat? |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| FY2023 | Up **8% to 9%** in constant currency | Up **10%** in constant currency; Adjusted diluted EPS **$4.30** | **Yes** — beat top end by ~1 ppt |
| FY2024 | Up **4% to 5%** in constant currency | Up **6%** in constant currency; Adjusted diluted EPS **$4.52** | **Yes** — beat top end by ~1 ppt |

**Answer:** General Mills has beaten Adjusted Diluted EPS guidance **2 out of 2 times** in the past two completed fiscal years.

For **FY2025**, as of April 7, 2025, General Mills’ latest guidance is that **adjusted diluted EPS is expected to be down 8% to down 7% in constant currency**. This was lowered from the prior range of down 4% to down 2%. Based on FY2024 adjusted diluted EPS of **$4.52**, that implies approximately **$4.16 to $4.20** in FY2025 adjusted diluted EPS, before any currency effects.

Calculation for implied FY2025 EPS range:
- Low end: $4.52 × (1 − 8%) = **$4.16**
- High end: $4.52 × (1 − 7%) = **$4.20**

Note: If “guidance” is interpreted as **initial guidance at the start of each fiscal year**, FY2023 beat its initial range, while FY2024 finished at the high end of its initial 4%–6% range rather than above it. The 2-for-2 count above uses the more common comparison to the latest management guidance before final results.

